node.text:
The London Contemporary Orchestra performing Isobel Waller-Bridge’s Arise at the Alexander McQueen Spring/Summer 2020 show.
As part of our #McQueenCreators series we will be sharing #McQueenMusic with you.

Visit our Spotify channel to hear playlists inspired by Alexander McQueen shows and featuring their soundtracks. 
Follow the link in our bio to listen to our #McQueenMusic playlists.

The Alexander McQueen Autumn/Winter 2020 show in Paris. “The collection is a love letter to women and to families, colleagues and friends. We went to Wales and were inspired by the warmth of its artistic and poetic heritage, by its folklore and the soul of its craft. The woman is courageous, grounded, bold: heroic. There is a sense of protection in the clothes, of safety and comfort, evoked through quilting and blankets. The hearts are a symbol of togetherness, of being there for others.” Sarah Burton Creative Director 
#McQueenAW20 #PFW #AlexanderMcQueen

node.text:
Follow Head of Atelier, Judy Halil, as she gives a step-by-step demonstration and insight into the expertise of the studio at Alexander McQueen.

Here she makes one of the centrepieces of the Roses installation: the swirling red Rose dress by Sarah Burton from the Autumn/Winter 2019 collection.

Visit the installation at #27OldBondStreet, our London flagship.

Video by @MashaVasyukova.

#AlexanderMcQueen

node.title: Alexander McQueen Spring/Summer 2019 Menswear Show Highlights

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Alexander McQueen on July 20, 2021 tagging @alexandermcqueen. May be an image of 1 person and standing.

node.text:
#JunJiHyun wearing a #McQueenAW21 washed polytaffeta deep v-neck drawstring dress with gathered channels and ribbon ties to the Kingdom, Ashin of the North #Netflix press conference in Korea.

#SeenInMcQueen

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Alexander McQueen on July 19, 2021 tagging @alexandermcqueen.

node.text:
Overblown rose volumes with fine tucks in black silk taffeta combine to create the voluminous proportions and undulating folds of this dress, reminiscent of blooming flowers.

From the Autumn/Winter 2019 collection, now displayed at the #McQueenRoses installation at #27OldBondStreet, our London flagship.

Photographed by @ChloeLeDrezen.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Alexander McQueen on July 19, 2021 tagging @alexandermcqueen.
Photo by Alexander McQueen on July 19, 2021. May be an image of one or more people.
Photo by Alexander McQueen on July 19, 2021.
Photo shared by Alexander McQueen on July 18, 2021 tagging @alexandermcqueen.

node.text:
Toiles of the AW19 swirling red Rose dress.⁣
⁣
The silhouette was initially draped on the house model by Sarah Burton and her studio team.⁣
⁣
The techniques needed to capture the abundant asymmetry of a natural rose. These were devised with Sarah and Judy Halil, Head of the Atelier, in an intensive process of pin-tucking in the neckline and free-form gathering of whorls in the volume of the skirt.⁣
⁣
The #McQueenRoses installation can be seen at #27OldBondStreet, our London flagship.⁣
⁣
Photograph by @ChloeLeDrezen.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Alexander McQueen on July 18, 2021. May be an image of rose.

node.text:
The finale dress from the Spring ‘07 Sarabande collection.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
The collection stemmed from a lyrical stream of consciousness about a ‘decadent and decaying grandeur’, which McQueen wanted to manifest against the backdrop of a ‘deserted theatre.’⁣⁣
⁣⁣
See the Sarabande collection at the #McQueenRoses installation inside #27OldBondStreet, our London flagship.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Photograph by @ChloeLeDrezen.
